article.headline: Oregon St. 51, Washington 46
article.story:
SEATTLE --  Sage Indendi scored 17 points, including five 3-pointers, to help lead Oregon State past Washington 51-46 Saturday, snapping a 10-game losing streak.

El Sara Greer added 10 points, 10 rebounds and three blocks for the Beavers (8-14, 1-10 Pac-10), which had last won on Dec. 21.

Regina Rogers scored 17 points and pulled down a career-high 12 rebounds to lead the Huskies (9-11, 4-7), which had won two in a row.

Indendi hit three 3-pointers in the second half to hold off Washington, who reached no closer than four points in the second half after trailing by nine at halftime.

Oregon State won despite making just 10 of 24 free throws (41.7 percent). Washington shot 2 of 12 (16.7 percent) on 3-pointers.

Kristi Kingma shot just 3 of 11 from the field and finished with eight points for the Huskies. She shot 2 of 8 on 3-pointers.

Rogers scored an inside basket to cut the Oregon State lead to 45-41 with 1:40 remaining. But Alyssa Martin made four free throws to keep the Beavers ahead.

Martin converted a three-point play to give the Beavers a 39-27 lead with 11:03 left in the game.

The Beavers went scoreless over the next six minutes, but still kept a seven-point lead as Washington scored just five points.

Indendi scored eight to help give Oregon State a 28-19 halftime lead. The Beavers led by as much as 13 in the first half.

The Huskies went 11 minutes without a field goal in the first half before Rogers made a layup with 3:12 left. They shot 6 of 21 (28.6 percent) from the field in the first half and finished 16 of 45 (35.6 percent).
